1. Base = Python 3.xxx
2. mkdir /code   ,,,  /root /src/ /users/
3. WORKDIR /code
4. COPY ALL -> CONTAINER
5. pip install requirements.txt
5. ./manage.py runserver 
6. EXPOSE 8000


1. Building an Image.
2. Running a container from that image.
3. Making changes to the Image.
4. Running again the image an verifying the changes.
------------------
5. Running the same image using docker-compose.
6. Exposing a port in docker compose.
7. Volumes in Docker compose
